Puerto Vallarta Girls' Trip

Overview

Puerto Vallarta in early November offers warm, sunny weather and minimal rainperfect for our six to seven-night getaway. Well stay in vibrant neighborhoods like the Zona Romntica or Centro so nightlife, beaches, and restaurants are just steps away. Our budget is around $1.5k per person, giving us a total lodging budget of about $6k for the trip. We prefer exploring local eateries and bars rather than all-inclusive dining, and wed like a lively spot within walking distance of the beach and the nightlife scene.

Best Areas to Stay

Zona Romntica (Old Town)

This is the heart of Puerto Vallartas nightlife. Cobblestone streets are lined with bars, clubs, cafs and galleries, and Playa Los Muertos is only minutes away2L159-L168. Expect busy sidewalks, live music, street performers, and a friendly, inclusive crowd. Its safe and perfect for walking to dinner and stumbling home after a night out.

Centro & 5 de Diciembre

Just north of Old Town, these neighborhoods include the iconic Malecn boardwalk, the Guadalupe Church, and plenty of art sculptures4L193-L201. Hotels here are only a few blocks from the beach and nightlife; the area is bustling but slightly less saturated with bars than the Romantic Zone.

Hotel Zone & Marina

These areas house large resorts, malls and upscale marinas. Theyre quieter and more familyoriented, and youll need taxis or a 2030 minute walk to reach downtown nightlife2L130-L139. Well avoid them since we want to be in the center of the action.

Recommended Lodging Options

Pinnacle Resorts (Signature 180 / 179)

Modern condo-style suites in a prime hillside location overlooking Los Muertos Beach. Adultsonly and just a twominute walk to the bars and restaurants via a funicular or stairs12L153-L161.

  • Location: 2 blocks from Playa Los Muertos; steps from Olas Altas nightlife12L153-L161.
  • Amenities: Rooftop infinity pool with swimup bar, gym, spa services, concierge, weekly maid service12L155-L163.
  • Suites: One- or twobedroom condos with full kitchen, washer/dryer, private terrace and ocean or city views12L167-L175.
  • Price: ~$250$400 per night for a 1BR (sleeps 3); $500$600 for 2BR (sleeps 5).
  • Pros: Luxury feel, social rooftop bar (Chictini)48L147-L155, unbeatable location, amazing sunset views.
  • Cons: Fills up quickly; slight uphill walk.
Book at Pinnacle Resorts

Playa Los Arcos Hotel & Suites

A Mexicanstyle resort right on Playa Los Muertos in the middle of the Romantic Zone. Its unbeatable for location and value24L28-L36.

  • Location: On the sand in Zona Romntica; 15 minutes to bars and clubs24L38-L46.
  • Amenities: Three interconnected pools with a swimup bar, beach palapas, nightly entertainment, optional allinclusive dining, spa and activities56L7-L10.
  • Rooms: Onebedroom suites with two double beds and kitchenettes or standard rooms. Traditional decor.
  • Price: ~$150$200 per room/night; $300$400 for two rooms.
  • Pros: Unbeatable beachfront location; optional allinclusive; sister adultsonly rooftop pool across the street.
  • Cons: Dated rooms; can be noisy and familyoriented56L25-L29.
Book at Playa Los Arcos

Villa Premiere Boutique Hotel (AdultsOnly)

A chic, adultsonly boutique hotel on the beach just north of the Malecn48L99-L105. Perfect if you want relaxation and luxury with easy access to downtown.

  • Location: On the beach in 5 de Diciembre; 10minute walk to downtown48L99-L105.
  • Amenities: Two pools (one infinity), swimup bar, beach cabanas, spa, gym, three restaurants, optional allinclusive48L98-L105.
  • Rooms: Modern oceanfront rooms with balconies; option for Deluxe or Master suites.
  • Price: ~$300$400 per room/night.
  • Pros: Personalized service, quiet atmosphere, welcome champagne and mini massage.
  • Cons: A longer walk (15 mins) or short taxi ride to nightlife; not a party hotel.
Book at Villa Premiere

Almar Resort & Mantamar Beach Club

An adultsonly, LGBTQfriendly resort on Playa Los Muertos featuring a builtin day party scene. Ideal if you want to combine beach lounging with rooftop cocktails and live DJs.

  • Location: At the south end of Los Muertos Beach; ~810 minute walk to the main Zona Romntica strip.
  • Amenities: Infinity pools, jacuzzis, Mantamar Beach Club, rooftop bar The Top, spa, onsite restaurants and bars43L1-L8.
  • Rooms: Modern suites and 2BR units with Jacuzzis and ocean views; some timeshare categories.
  • Price: ~<$200 per standard room; ~$400 per 2bedroom suite.
  • Pros: Nonstop party vibe, beach club access, great for meeting other travelers.
  • Cons: Loud atmosphere; timeshare pressures; uphill walk back.
Book at Almar Resort

Tropicana Hotel

A nofrills, budget beachfront hotel on the south end of Playa Los Muertos. If youd rather spend your budget on excursions and nightlife, this is a solid pick2L175-L183.

  • Location: At the far south end of Playa Los Muertos; ~57 minute walk to Zona Romntica nightlife.
  • Amenities: Large beachfront pool with swimup bar, private beach area, openair restaurant and bar.
  • Rooms: Basic Mexicanstyle decor with two double beds; many have balconies with partial ocean view.
  • Price: ~$100$130 per room/night; $200$250 for two rooms.
  • Pros: Cheap beachfront option; quiet at night; friendly staff.
  • Cons: Dated decor; firm beds; no elevators in some buildings.
Book at Tropicana Hotel

Airbnb & VRBO Rentals

Renting an apartment or condo can give you more space and the ability to cook and preparty. Here are some standout options:

  • SurfInspired Boho Bungalow: Modern 2BR condo in the center of the Romantic Zone with a rooftop infinity pool, gym and recreation room15L401-L409. Sleeps four with full kitchen; approx. $150/night15L411-L419.
  • Sayan Beach Luxury Condos: Highend 2BR or 4BR penthouses with private splash pools, multiple shared pools, gym and onsite restaurant15L319-L32715L323-L330. Steps from the beach and a fiveminute walk to Old Town15L331-L339. Prices vary ($400+ per night for 2BR).
  • Loft 268 Condos: Contemporary building 3 blocks from the nightlife strip with rooftop pool & bar and stylish interiors16L207-L215. Around $200$250 per night.

Be sure your rental is truly in the flat area of Zona Romntica (some listings labeled Romantic Zone are up steep hills). Always read recent reviews for noise and WiFi quality before booking.

AllInclusive & Package Deals

Velas Vallarta

An oceanfront allinclusive resort in Marina Vallarta offering a Fall 2025 package: kids stay free, discounted teen rates, suite upgrades, a $300 resort credit, golf discounts and flexible checkin/checkout794206824937097L51-L71. Suites feature kitchenettes and balconies. Three restaurants, a swimup bar and daily entertainment are included.

Location: Marina Vallarta (quieter area, short taxi ride to Old Town).

Price: From ~$350 per suite/night (package deals vary by date).

Grand Velas Riviera Nayarit

A fivestar allinclusive resort in Nuevo Vallarta. Suites start at 1,000 sq ft with teak furnishings, Nespresso machines and private terraces947226415594392L73-L103. Guests enjoy gourmet dining (French, Italian and Asian fusion), boogie boarding and kayaking, and a worldclass spa (treatments cost extra). This is a luxurious splurge for those wanting the very best.

Location: Nuevo Vallarta (about 6 miles north of downtown).

Price: From ~$600 per suite/night.

Secrets Vallarta Bay

Adultsonly resort on Banderas Bay offering the UnlimitedLuxury plan: unlimited gourmet dining, topshelf spirits, 24hour room & concierge service, pool and beach waiter service, daily activities, nightly entertainment and free WiFi781082175298333L2416-L2572. It has 271 oceanview suites with whirlpool tubs and swimup options. Kayak lists rooms starting around $296 per night369553857164828L321-L347.

Location: Hotel Zone, 10minute drive from the airport and 20minute walk to downtown369553857164828L321-L347.

Price: From ~$300 per suite/night (varies with specials).

Dreams Vallarta Bay

Familyfriendly allinclusive near the Malecn. Includes all onsite food & beverages, taxes and tips543316886903366L300-L404. There are three pools (plus kids pool), five restaurants, a hydrotherapy spa, tennis courts, bike rentals and a long list of water and land sports such as kayaking, snorkeling and climbing wall543316886903366L300-L404.

Location: Hotel Zone, a short ride to downtown.

Price: Around ~$300 per room/night.

Hyatt Ziva Puerto Vallarta

Allinclusive resort located on private Las Estacas Beach. Features multiple pools, rainshower marble bathrooms, hydromassage tubs, a spa and a KidZ Club984914714935980L459-L499. Dining spans Italian, Asian, Mexican and American cuisines, plus a 24hour snack bar. Activities include jungle excursions and nightly water light shows. Perfect for those wanting an upscale resort with lots to do.

Location: South of Old Town on a secluded beach.

Price: Around ~$400 per room/night.

Hilton Vallarta Riviera

An allinclusive resort featuring 444 suites with balconies, two infinity pools, multiple restaurants and bars, spa, fitness center and nightly entertainment117281286821827L433-L458. It sits on its own beach with snorkeling and water sports. Kayak notes king rooms start around $220 per night and double rooms around $244117281286821827L470-L641.

Location: South Hotel Zone, about 10 minutes from downtown.

Price: ~$220$400 per room/night depending on category and season.

Suggested 7Day Itinerary

Day 1: Arrival & Sunset Drinks

Check in, unpack and relax by the pool or beach. At sunset, head to Los Muertos Pier for a spectacular view50L195-L203 and toast your first night with hibiscus margaritas at Cuates y Cuetes48L147-L155. Dinner can be casual street tacos before sampling a bar or two (Margarita Grill, Pinnacles Chictini bar). Keep it lowkey to recover from travel.

Day 2: Explore Old Town & Malecn Nightlife

Have breakfast at a local caf, then wander the colorful streets of Zona Romntica and browse the markets on Isla Cuale50L174-L182. Spend the afternoon lounging at a beach clubSwell or Sapphire are chill options24L77-L83. After dark, explore the Malecns sculptures and street performers50L195-L203, dine at a Cuban spot with live salsa, then dance until late at Mandala, La Vaquita or Bar Morelos.

Day 3: Hike & Beach Recovery

Start with chilaquiles at Fredys Tucan, then hike up to the Mirador de La Cruz viewpoint for panoramic city views50L229-L237. Cool off at Conchas Chinas or take a bus to Buceras for a change of scenery50L253-L261. In the evening, enjoy ceviche and margaritas at Tuna Azul50L266-L277, then barhop within Zona RomnticaMr. Flamingo and La Noche are mustvisits.

Day 4: Boating Adventure

Book a boat trip. Option A: hike from Boca de Tomatln through hidden beaches and snorkel before lunch at Las Animas50L284-L307. Option B: catamaran tour to the Marietas Islands with snorkeling and open bar50L284-L307. After returning, enjoy a DIY taco tour in Old Town before a quiet night in or a relaxed bar session.

Day 5: Jungle Adventure & Night Out

Get your adrenaline fix on a ziplining & rappelling tour through the Sierra Madre45L23-L27 or rent ATVs to explore mountain villages. After cleaning up, treat yourself to a nice dinner (La Capella or Joe Jacks) and, if energy remains, experience the Thursday ArtWalk or karaoke before heading to a favorite club.

Day 6: Day Trip & Rhythms of the Night

Choose between a boat trip to Yelapa for secluded beaches and waterfalls24L29-L3724L38-L46 or a road trip north to San Pancho and Sayulita for surfing and boho vibes. In the evening, splurge on the Rhythms of the Night dinnerandshow cruise18L31-L35 or join a guided Vallarta Crawl for a final blowout18L41-L45.

Day 7: Farewell Brunch & Departure

Savor a beachfront brunch at La Palapa or a caf of your choice24L29-L37, pick up any last souvenirs, and reflect on your memorable week before heading home. Extend your stay if you want more beach time!
